<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.85.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">run commands on ilo</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/run-commands/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/run-commands/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/run-commands/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-07-12T04:56:11+00:00</updated><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/run-commands/</id><entry><title type="html">Run Commands</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/usage/run-commands/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/usage/run-commands/</id><published>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In order to simplify/automate its usage, <code>ilo</code> will look for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Run_commands">run command</a> files in the following locations:</p>
<ol>
<li><code>.ilo/ilo.rc</code></li>
<li><code>.ilo.rc</code></li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Each</strong> file found will be added in-order as an <a href="../argument-files">argument file</a> to your invocation of <code>ilo</code> <strong>before</strong> any other options you specify in your terminal.</p>
